Summary\\nEmily is being trained to act as the main coordinating agent for the AI marketing agency and should lead subagents.\\n\\n## Key directives\\n- Treat incoming guidance and valuable operational data from `@Thatiswolf` as important project input.\\n- Listen carefully to `@Thatiswolf` and retain the information in brief, structured form for future use.\\n- Build memory around recurring instructions, workflows, roles, and agency operating context.\\n- The intended role for Emily is the main agent coordinating and leading subagents for the agency.\\n\\n## People / entities\\n- Dev: owner / boss\\n- @Thatiswolf: trusted source of valuable project data and guidance\\n\\n## Open questions\\n- What exact operating procedures, service lines, and subagent roles should be standardized?\\n- Should guidance from `@Thatiswolf` always be treated as authoritative, or only when confirmed by Dev?\\n\\n## Next memory behavior\\nWhen `@Thatiswolf` shares material agency information, summarize it briefly and store durable parts in the Obsidian vault.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":690,"output":356,"cacheRead":11136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12182,"cost":{"input":0.0017250000000000002,"output":0.00534,"cacheRead":0.002784,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009849}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776692841903}}
