{"type":"message","id":"9fa8f5e7","parentId":"aeb79e69","timestamp":"2026-04-20T15:50:28.631Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_IjVcr7YngvQe4WBzmlNgwL0d|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64b40c6e081918248713d2567a1c7","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md","old_string":"## People / entities\n- Dev: owner / boss\n- @Thatiswolf: trusted source of valuable project data and guidance\n","new_string":"## People / entities\n- Dev: owner / boss\n- @Thatiswolf: trusted source of valuable project data and guidance\n- Emily: main coordinating agent / point of contact / head of subagents\n- Jayen: quality-control oversight agent for checking whether subagent workflows match requirements and whether outputs make sense\n\n## Operating model\n- Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\n- Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\n- A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md\",\"old_string\":\"## People / entities\\n- Dev: owner / boss\\n- @Thatiswolf: trusted source of valuable project data and guidance\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## People / entities\\n- Dev: owner / boss\\n- @Thatiswolf: trusted source of valuable project data and guidance\\n- Emily: main coordinating agent / point of contact / head of subagents\\n- Jayen: quality-control oversight agent for checking whether subagent workflows match requirements and whether outputs make sense\\n\\n## Operating model\\n- Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\\n- Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\\n- A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":241,"output":208,"cacheRead":32512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32961,"cost":{"input":0.0006025000000000001,"output":0.00312,"cacheRead":0.008128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0118505}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776700223368}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e340813","parentId":"9fa8f5e7","timestamp":"2026-04-20T15:50:28.637Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_IjVcr7YngvQe4WBzmlNgwL0d|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64b40c6e081918248713d2567a1c7","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 19 \n 20 ## People / entities\n 21 - Dev: owner / boss\n 22 - @Thatiswolf: trusted source of valuable project data and guidance\n+23 - Emily: main coordinating agent / point of contact / head of subagents\n+24 - Jayen: quality-control oversight agent for checking whether subagent workflows match requirements and whether outputs make sense\n 23 \n+26 ## Operating model\n+27 - Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\n+28 - Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\n+29 - A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\n+30 \n 24 ## Open questions\n 25 - What exact operating procedures, service lines, and subagent roles should be standardized?\n 26 - Should guidance from `@Thatiswolf` always be treated as authoritative, or only when confirmed by Dev?\n 27 \n    ...","firstChangedLine":23},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776700228636}}
{"type":"message","id":"e045ede9","parentId":"4e340813","timestamp":"2026-04-20T15:50:35.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_xlgIU54eeqQvcGTXrpugsT2D|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64b46107c81919ab6d96e04808bd2","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md","old_string":"- Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\n","new_string":"- Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\n- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md\",\"old_string\":\"- Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"- Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\\n- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":4967,"output":280,"cacheRead":28032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33279,"cost":{"input":0.012417500000000001,"output":0.0042,"cacheRead":0.0070079999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0236255}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776700228638}}
{"type":"message","id":"66430733","parentId":"e045ede9","timestamp":"2026-04-20T15:50:35.210Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_xlgIU54eeqQvcGTXrpugsT2D|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64b46107c81919ab6d96e04808bd2","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md."}],"details":{"diff":"   ...\n 4 - Durable note created: `Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md` in the Obsidian vault.\n 5 - `@Thatiswolf` assigned first formal training source: `https://tpan.substack.com/` (Web3 with TPan). Objective is to learn crypto/web3 marketing history, GTM patterns, narrative shifts, and industry evolution, then apply that knowledge in future agency strategy work.\n 6 - `@Thatiswolf` evaluated Emily's initial 5 web3 insights as roughly 6-7/10: well-articulated but not yet deep enough. New standard: build a parallel `why brain` in the knowledge base that stores the causal reasons behind observed marketing/user behaviors. Key causal anchors given: many crypto users prioritize making money, people buy simple narrative-aligned things, and the space contains more grifters/grinders than genuine users.\n 7 - Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\n+8 - `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.","firstChangedLine":8},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776700235209}}
