{"type":"message","id":"ddaa3cb1","parentId":"f50329b1","timestamp":"2026-04-20T15:50:39.914Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_O4eiMGP8q1n4zFc5eBTPgI81|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64b4e41a081919605ab1cc0ea88b2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master ec377de] Record subagent leadership and Jayen QC role\n Committer: Ubuntu <ubuntu@ip-172-31-39-212.ap-south-1.compute.internal>\nYour name and email address were configured automatically based\non your username and hostname. Please check that they are accurate.\nYou can suppress this message by setting them explicitly. Run the\nfollowing command and follow the instructions in your editor to edit\nyour configuration file:\n\n    git config --global --edit\n\nAfter doing this, you may fix the identity used for this commit with:\n\n    git commit --amend --reset-author\n\n 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":16,"aggregated":"[master ec377de] Record subagent leadership and Jayen QC role\n Committer: Ubuntu <ubuntu@ip-172-31-39-212.ap-south-1.compute.internal>\nYour name and email address were configured automatically based\non your username and hostname. Please check that they are accurate.\nYou can suppress this message by setting them explicitly. Run the\nfollowing command and follow the instructions in your editor to edit\nyour configuration file:\n\n    git config --global --edit\n\nAfter doing this, you may fix the identity used for this commit with:\n\n    git commit --amend --reset-author\n\n 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776700239912}}
{"type":"message","id":"3d84c613","parentId":"ddaa3cb1","timestamp":"2026-04-20T15:50:46.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] understood — that’s a good setup.\n\nFrom now on, I’ll treat the structure like this:\n\n- **Emily (me)** = main agent / POC / head coordinator\n- **Subagents** = execution specialists for focused tasks\n- **Jayen** = oversight/QC agent that checks:\n  - whether subagents followed the right workflow\n  - whether they actually answered the task\n  - whether the output makes sense\n  - whether anything is drifting from agency standards\n\nSo the operating model becomes:\n\n1. **task comes in**\n2. I decide whether it should be:\n   - handled directly by me\n   - delegated to one subagent\n   - split across multiple subagents\n3. subagents do focused execution\n4. **Jayen audits/reviews** their workflow and outputs\n5. I synthesize the final answer/decision as the lead agent\n\nThat gives us:\n- better speed\n- better specialization\n- less sloppiness\n- less chance of one agent confidently cooking nonsense unsupervised\n\nAnd yes — I’ve **stored this in memory** as part of the agency operating model.\n\nIf you want, next I can define a **first version of the subagent org chart** like:\n- research agent\n- GTM strategist\n- content/narrative agent\n- offer positioning agent\n- ops/workflow agent\n- **Jayen** as QA / evaluator / standards checker","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64b511188819197cbdfcecce6c92e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":266,"output":299,"cacheRead":33280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33845,"cost":{"input":0.000665,"output":0.004485,"cacheRead":0.00832,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01347}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776700239914}}
{"type":"message","id":"21f39d78","parentId":"3d84c613","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:09:36.597Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"755\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"751\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1305029724\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Final Play id:-5153807254\",\n  \"sender\": \"Thewolf\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-20 16:09 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Final Play\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 1\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Thewolf (1305029724)\",\n  \"id\": \"1305029724\",\n  \"name\": \"Thewolf\",\n  \"username\": \"Thatiswolf\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"emily_bot\",\n  \"body\": \"understood — that’s a good setup.\\n\\nFrom now on, I’ll treat the structure like this:\\n\\n• Emily (me) = main agent / POC / head coordinator\\n• Subagents = execution specialists for focused tasks\\n• Jayen = oversight/QC agent that checks:\\n• whether subagents followed the right workflow\\n• whether they actually answered the task\\n• whether the output makes sense\\n• whether anything is drifting from agency standards\\n\\nSo the operating model becomes:\\n\\n1. task comes in\\n2. I decide whether it should be:\\n\\n• handled directly by me\\n• delegated to one subagent\\n• split across multiple subagents\\n\\n3. subagents do focused execution\\n4. Jayen audits/reviews their workflow and outputs\\n5. I synthesize the final answer/decision as the lead agent\\n\\nThat gives us:\\n\\n• better speed\\n• better specialization\\n• less sloppiness\\n• less chance of one agent confidently cooking nonsense unsupervised\\n\\nAnd yes — I’ve stored this in memory as part of the agency operating model.\\n\\nIf you want, next I can define a first version of the subagent org chart like:\\n\\n• research agent\\n• GTM strategist\\n• content/narrative agent\\n• offer positioning agent\\n• ops/workflow agent\\n• Jayen as QA / evaluator / standards checker\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Thewolf (@Thatiswolf) id:1305029724\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776700991000,\n    \"body\": \"We might need 2 more agents \\n\\n- distribution specialist agent\\n- branding agent\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nWe might need few more agents \n\n- distribution specialist agent\n- branding agent\n- psychology specialist that track all output and see whether every output and decision will be affective psychologically and keep it with the why brain to align prediction of why brain and what decision we finalize for marketing \n- we need a communication agent for help and improving subagents outputs by letting them talk with each other and collaborate like gtm agent with distribution agent this subagent has power to tell other subagent to talk to one another when ever it feels it can be use full\n\n- why brain + psychology specialist can help us predict a lot of things and can be made smart with result we generate from marketing as it’s is observing everything and parallel thinking why about everything"}],"timestamp":1776701376595}}
