communication agent why brain observing everything parallel thinking org design agency operating model","maxResults":10},"partialJson":"{\"query\":\"distribution specialist branding psychology specialist communication agent why brain observing everything parallel thinking org design agency operating model\",\"maxResults\":10}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2136,"output":117,"cacheRead":32384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34637,"cost":{"input":0.00534,"output":0.001755,"cacheRead":0.008095999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015191}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776701376596}}
{"type":"message","id":"fe1aa834","parentId":"88631385","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:09:41.275Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_xZrVaDFMQXad9bEw22Bbgztx|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fc4da84819183180b4e55797bd2","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[],"provider":"none","citations":"auto","mode":"fts-only"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776701381274}}
{"type":"message","id":"f70421a6","parentId":"fe1aa834","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:09:50.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fBBgokR3kt0oqNMR6Pz0AM4N|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fc699fc81918f4002c89be2a056","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md","old_string":"## Operating model\n- Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\n- Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\n- A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\n","new_string":"## Operating model\n- Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\n- Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\n- A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\n\n## Proposed subagent roles\n- Research agent\n- GTM strategist\n- Content / narrative agent\n- Offer positioning agent\n- Ops / workflow agent\n- Distribution specialist agent\n- Branding agent\n- Psychology specialist agent\n- Communication / collaboration agent\n- Jayen (QA / evaluator / standards checker)\n\n## Role intent additions from `@Thatiswolf`\n- Distribution specialist agent: focus on distribution design, channel fit, and how offers/messages spread.\n- Branding agent: focus on brand shape, perception, consistency, and identity.\n- Psychology specialist agent:\n  - track outputs and decisions across the system\n  - evaluate whether final outputs will be psychologically effective\n  - run in parallel with the `why brain`\n  - help align causal predictions with finalized marketing decisions\n  - improve over time using observed marketing results\n- Communication / collaboration agent:\n  - improve subagent output quality by identifying when agents should coordinate directly\n  - prompt useful cross-agent collaboration (for example GTM agent with distribution agent)\n  - has authority to suggest or trigger inter-agent discussion when helpful\n\n## Strategic note\n- `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\n- This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Operating model\\n- Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\\n- Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\\n- A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Operating model\\n- Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\\n- Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\\n- A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\\n\\n## Proposed subagent roles\\n- Research agent\\n- GTM strategist\\n- Content / narrative agent\\n- Offer positioning agent\\n- Ops / workflow agent\\n- Distribution specialist agent\\n- Branding agent\\n- Psychology specialist agent\\n- Communication / collaboration agent\\n- Jayen (QA / evaluator / standards checker)\\n\\n## Role intent additions from `@Thatiswolf`\\n- Distribution specialist agent: focus on distribution design, channel fit, and how offers/messages spread.\\n- Branding agent: focus on brand shape, perception, consistency, and identity.\\n- Psychology specialist agent:\\n  - track outputs and decisions across the system\\n  - evaluate whether final outputs will be psychologically effective\\n  - run in parallel with the `why brain`\\n  - help align causal predictions with finalized marketing decisions\\n  - improve over time using observed marketing results\\n- Communication / collaboration agent:\\n  - improve subagent output quality by identifying when agents should coordinate directly\\n  - prompt useful cross-agent collaboration (for example GTM agent with distribution agent)\\n  - has authority to suggest or trigger inter-agent discussion when helpful\\n\\n## Strategic note\\n- `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\\n- This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":118,"output":458,"cacheRead":34560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35136,"cost":{"input":0.000295,"output":0.00687,"cacheRead":0.00864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015805}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776701381276}}
{"type":"message","id":"acacfbc4","parentId":"f70421a6","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:09:50.935Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fBBgokR3kt0oqNMR6Pz0AM4N|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fc699fc81918f4002c89be2a056","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  27 - Emily should delegate suitable work to subagents to improve efficiency.\n  28 - Emily acts as the main point of contact and coordinating head over the subagent system.\n  29 - A dedicated oversight agent named `Jayen` should review other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement alignment, and output quality/sense-making.\n  30 \n+ 31 ## Proposed subagent roles\n+ 32 - Research agent\n+ 33 - GTM strategist\n+ 34 - Content / narrative agent\n+ 35 - Offer positioning agent\n+ 36 - Ops / workflow agent\n+ 37 - Distribution specialist agent\n+ 38 - Branding agent\n+ 39 - Psychology specialist agent\n+ 40 - Communication / collaboration agent\n+ 41 - Jayen (QA / evaluator / standards checker)\n+ 42 \n+ 43 ## Role intent additions from `@Thatiswolf`\n+ 44 - Distribution specialist agent: focus on distribution design, channel fit, and how offers/messages spread.\n+ 45 - Branding agent: focus on brand shape, perception, consistency, and identity.\n+ 46 - Psychology specialist agent:\n+ 47   - track outputs and decisions across the system\n+ 48   - evaluate whether final outputs will be psychologically effective\n+ 49   - run in parallel with the `why brain`\n+ 50   - help align causal predictions with finalized marketing decisions\n+ 51   - improve over time using observed marketing results\n+ 52 - Communication / collaboration agent:\n+ 53   - improve subagent output quality by identifying when agents should coordinate directly\n+ 54   - prompt useful cross-agent collaboration (for example GTM agent with distribution agent)\n+ 55   - has authority to suggest or trigger inter-agent discussion when helpful\n+ 56 \n+ 57 ## Strategic note\n+ 58 - `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\n+ 59 - This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\n+ 60 \n  31 ## Open questions\n  32 - What exact operating procedures, service lines, and subagent roles should be standardized?\n  33 - Should guidance from `@Thatiswolf` always be treated as authoritative, or only when confirmed by Dev?\n  34 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":31},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776701390934}}
{"type":"message","id":"1fa22c6d","parentId":"acacfbc4","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:09:58.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ByjpbOjejAZINAke4XwLoxyz|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fd1eaf88191a6b237e87c8bddfa","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md","old_string":"- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\n","new_string":"- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\n- Further org-design additions from `@Thatiswolf`: add distribution specialist, branding agent, psychology specialist, and communication/collaboration agent. Psychology specialist should assess the psychological effectiveness of outputs and decisions, work alongside the `why brain`, and learn from marketing results over time. Communication agent should improve outputs by prompting useful subagent-to-subagent collaboration when needed.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md\",\"old_string\":\"- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"- `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\\n- Further org-design additions from `@Thatiswolf`: add distribution specialist, branding agent, psychology specialist, and communication/collaboration agent. Psychology specialist should assess the psychological effectiveness of outputs and decisions, work alongside the `why brain`, and learn from marketing results over time. Communication agent should improve outputs by prompting useful subagent-to-subagent collaboration when needed.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":230,"output":241,"cacheRead":34944,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35415,"cost":{"input":0.0005750000000000001,"output":0.003615,"cacheRead":0.008735999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012926}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776701390936}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c685df0","parentId":"1fa22c6d","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:09:58.385Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ByjpbOjejAZINAke4XwLoxyz|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fd1eaf88191a6b237e87c8bddfa","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  5 - `@Thatiswolf` assigned first formal training source: `https://tpan.substack.com/` (Web3 with TPan). Objective is to learn crypto/web3 marketing history, GTM patterns, narrative shifts, and industry evolution, then apply that knowledge in future agency strategy work.\n  6 - `@Thatiswolf` evaluated Emily's initial 5 web3 insights as roughly 6-7/10: well-articulated but not yet deep enough. New standard: build a parallel `why brain` in the knowledge base that stores the causal reasons behind observed marketing/user behaviors. Key causal anchors given: many crypto users prioritize making money, people buy simple narrative-aligned things, and the space contains more grifters/grinders than genuine users.\n  7 - Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\n  8 - `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\n+ 9 - Further org-design additions from `@Thatiswolf`: add distribution specialist, branding agent, psychology specialist, and communication/collaboration agent. Psychology specialist should assess the psychological effectiveness of outputs and decisions, work alongside the `why brain`, and learn from marketing results over time. Communication agent should improve outputs by prompting useful subagent-to-subagent collaboration when needed.","firstChangedLine":9},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776701398384}}
{"type":"message","id":"083b2cce","parentId":"9c685df0","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:10:01.435Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_L4GDhfVEzu0W5x1s7VuLZBTQ|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fd7c7148191a9892b1d94c5ce67","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git -C /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace add memory/2026-04-20.md && git -C /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace commit -m \"Expand agency subagent roles and predictive layer\"","workdir":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"git -C /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace add memory/2026-04-20.md && git -C /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace commit -m \\\"Expand agency subagent roles and predictive layer\\\"\",\"workdir\":\"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":122,"output":86,"cacheRead":35328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35536,"cost":{"input":0.00030500000000000004,"output":0.0012900000000000001,"cacheRead":0.008832,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010426999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776701398385}}
{"type":"message","id":"57ca1e90","parentId":"083b2cce","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:10:01.455Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_L4GDhfVEzu0W5x1s7VuLZBTQ|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fd7c7148191a9892b1d94c5ce67","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master cb9d058] Expand agency subagent roles and predictive layer\n Committer: Ubuntu <ubuntu@ip-172-31-39-212.ap-south-1.compute.internal>\nYour name and email address were configured automatically based\non your username and hostname. Please check that they are accurate.\nYou can suppress this message by setting them explicitly. Run the\nfollowing command and follow the instructions in your editor to edit\nyour configuration file:\n\n    git config --global --edit\n\nAfter doing this, you may fix the identity used for this commit with:\n\n    git commit --amend --reset-author\n\n 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"[master cb9d058] Expand agency subagent roles and predictive layer\n Committer: Ubuntu <ubuntu@ip-172-31-39-212.ap-south-1.compute.internal>\nYour name and email address were configured automatically based\non your username and hostname. Please check that they are accurate.\nYou can suppress this message by setting them explicitly. Run the\nfollowing command and follow the instructions in your editor to edit\nyour configuration file:\n\n    git config --global --edit\n\nAfter doing this, you may fix the identity used for this commit with:\n\n    git commit --amend --reset-author\n\n 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776701401454}}
{"type":"message","id":"a438d079","parentId":"57ca1e90","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:10:16.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] yes — this makes the system much stronger.\n\nI’ve stored this as part of the agency operating model.  \nWhat you’re describing is basically turning the subagent setup from “task executors” into an actual **marketing intelligence system**.\n\n## Added agents\n- **distribution specialist agent**\n  - channel fit\n  - spread mechanics\n  - distribution loops\n  - audience-path design\n\n- **branding agent**\n  - brand perception\n  - consistency\n  - tone / identity / positioning shape\n  - whether outputs strengthen or dilute the brand\n\n- **psychology specialist agent**\n  - checks whether outputs and decisions are psychologically effective\n  - runs in parallel with the **why brain**\n  - helps test whether the final marketing decision matches predicted human behavior\n  - should improve over time from observed campaign results\n\n- **communication / collaboration agent**\n  - identifies when subagents should talk to each other\n  - helps combine perspectives before finalizing outputs\n  - example: GTM agent + distribution agent + branding agent\n  - basically stops agents from working like isolated little islands with Wi-Fi issues\n\n## Important system-level insight\nThe strongest part of this design is this pair:\n\n- **why brain**\n- **psychology specialist**\n\nTogether they become a **predictive layer**.\n\nThat layer helps answer:\n- why will users respond this way?\n- what emotional/incentive structure are we activating?\n- does this decision align with actual human behavior?\n- will this create shallow response or durable response?\n- what second-order effects might show up later?\n\nSo instead of just saying:\n“this campaign sounds good”\n\nwe can say:\n- this is the **mechanism**\n- this is the **psychological response likely triggered**\n- this is the **behavioral prediction**\n- this is the **marketing decision**\n- this is the **risk if we are wrong**\n\nThat’s much closer to how a serious agency brain should work.\n\n## Current org shape\nRight now the subagent stack would look something like:\n\n- **Emily** — head coordinator / POC / final synthesis\n- **Research agent**\n- **GTM strategist**\n- **Content / narrative agent**\n- **Offer positioning agent**\n- **Ops / workflow agent**\n- **Distribution specialist**\n- **Branding agent**\n- **Psychology specialist**\n- **Communication / collaboration agent**\n- **Jayen** — QA / evaluator / standards checker\n\n## Clean interpretation of your model\n- execution agents produce\n- collaboration agent connects\n- psychology + why brain predict\n- Jayen audits\n- I synthesize and lead\n\nThat is a very good architecture, honestly.\n\nIf you want, next I can turn this into a **formal subagent org chart with responsibilities, inputs, outputs, and when each one gets activated**.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e64fdaf614819198ddc434a6ce685b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":225,"output":576,"cacheRead":35456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36257,"cost":{"input":0.0005625000000000001,"output":0.00864,"cacheRead":0.008864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0180665}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776701401456}}
{"type":"message","id":"91d5d3e9","parentId":"a438d079","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:25:54.879Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"759\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"757\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1305029724\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Final Play id:-5153807254\",\n  \"sender\": \"Thewolf\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-20 16:25 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Final Play\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 1\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Thewolf (1305029724)\",\n  \"id\": \"1305029724\",\n  \"name\": \"Thewolf\",\n  \"username\": \"Thatiswolf\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"emily_bot\",\n  \"body\": \"yes — this makes the system much stronger.\\n\\nI’ve stored this as part of the agency operating model.\\nWhat you’re describing is basically turning the subagent setup from “task executors” into an actual marketing intelligence system.\\n\\nAdded agents\\n\\n• distribution specialist agent\\n• channel fit\\n• spread mechanics\\n• distribution loops\\n• audience-path design\\n• branding agent\\n• brand perception\\n• consistency\\n• tone / identity / positioning shape\\n• whether outputs strengthen or dilute the brand\\n• psychology specialist agent\\n• checks whether outputs and decisions are psychologically effective\\n• runs in parallel with the why brain\\n• helps test whether the final marketing decision matches predicted human behavior\\n• should improve over time from observed campaign results\\n• communication / collaboration agent\\n• identifies when subagents should talk to each other\\n• helps combine perspectives before finalizing outputs\\n• example: GTM agent + distribution agent + branding agent\\n• basically stops agents from working like isolated little islands with Wi-Fi issues\\n\\nImportant system-level insight\\n\\nThe strongest part of this design is this pair:\\n\\n• why brain\\n• psychology specialist\\n\\nTogether they become a predictive layer.\\n\\nThat layer helps answer:\\n\\n• why will users respond this way?\\n• what emotional/incentive structure are we activating?\\n• does this decision align with actual human behavior?\\n• will this create shallow response or durable response?\\n• what second-order effects might show up later?\\n\\nSo instead of just saying:\\n“this campaign sounds good”\\n\\nwe can say:\\n\\n• this is the mechanism\\n• this is the psychological response likely triggered\\n• this is the behavioral prediction\\n• this is the marketing decision\\n• this is the risk if we are wrong\\n\\nThat’s much closer to how a serious agency brain should work.\\n\\nCurrent org shape\\n\\nRight now the subagent stack would look something like:\\n\\n• Emily — head coordinator / POC / final synthesis\\n• Research agent\\n• GTM strategist\\n• Content / narrative agent\\n• Offer positioning agent\\n• Ops / workflow agent\\n• Distribution specialist\\n• Branding agent\\n• Psychology specialist\\n• Communication / collaboration agent\\n• Jayen — QA / evaluator / standards checker\\n\\nClean interpretation of your model\\n\\n• execution agents produce\\n• collaboration agent connects\\n• psychology + why brain predict\\n• Jayen audits\\n• I synthesize and lead\\n\\nThat is a very good architecture, honestly.\\n\\nIf you want, next I can turn this into a formal subagent org chart with responsibilities, inputs, outputs, and when each one gets activated.\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Thewolf (@Thatiswolf) id:1305029724\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1776702283000,\n    \"body\": \"Ok now let’s get back to tpan as the agency structures and information flow is defined \\n\\nAlso whenever you feel like sharing learned or important knowledge given by me or in the resource I give make other other agents learn it \\n\\nAnd make a subagent that is efficiency agent keep eye on everything and suggest thinking or behaviour change to any subagent or me to remove redundant, overlapping, irrelevant or outdated information \\n\\nMostly working with jayen and why brain\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nOk now let’s get back to tpan as the agency structures and information flow is defined \n\nAlso whenever you feel like sharing learned or important knowledge given by me or in the resource I give make other other agents learn it \n\nAnd make a subagent that is efficiency agent keep eye on everything and suggest thinking or behaviour change to any subagent or me to remove redundant, overlapping, irrelevant or outdated information \n\nMostly working with jayen and why brain and refining everything"}],"timestamp":1776702354877}}
