{"type":"message","id":"4c3001af","parentId":"0771acfc","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:59:11.026Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering memory and fixes**\n\nI need to confirm that I don't have any active subagents right now. Perhaps it's time to think about implementing some conceptual fixes, like selective activation and clearer boundaries. I'm wondering if I should also store a note about whether I need to implement these fixes. Writing in my memory might be a good idea, maybe even as a durable note. That way, I can keep track of what’s needed!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b5742a8819197044c6afe9f2899\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp5ltZDZ-pp-rznkXMohXv9O3Q4cJHHqawh9cdCCPZXoBOT-tr6oe7tZKRsIIL9whYHj4bSBJ41UVbBeK7WfvK8nDzK9ChBfLpRlMtyDPuSd8jDiJ5TS8r4W6oB9k7nsy8FE9O-FeNcTEWLdkd1OPCixZmg4_1Mf0kkMPwRrMVHGtWvHjUDSVuSEAhK6KBrYm1-925XSn6h7qDHGTx0ZtJrSuOQc5MiS2LvkA-RXpnhmYbu9qtoyrR_DJ_EZTJWHVS3w2wdbFE94QsEu6DvPdVpYbJ1g1WarmY6-ed8bV9KZKMlsizksEwzjMFctewKu2NtaRw7QL0W39OSaPga2jwR2LvqZLNMm4bvl1vDR0I6ZgpzpUF2gYBDwtWG68-_5u2cpzv5Eumpx0ei5gVykPMGobTUZJw_i1cI3tqtwrYgpy1XlBA4C6JLdbdRWMZkPolzEMAb7BZMefh38YuGOUam7k4I2Pb8QeidsUnzA01lgLY-Omwz4pixmkrMhjoC-2uzeHlaKfM5GIiI2F5PkFAMrIT-aWoqnc6utubW-VglzxOdud8QKkdL3obgQjqGV0Ub-WXIwtGI7jPNOx_DEcu2khbNWIGmuWwRpPq4E6IuivTvBGhOsoK0kBF9mZdi_POtSxizE_Ud1ufRIRae0SnJwnGSnzjPBeenz3cUGJjC80der9pXWevCQwsYVcSPVWeXO-trvQGMyCKUZDkP8lMLBs8_mcRAV2w9vVJdlnV_ccCwg0SnY83cOnb0Wuz7NHtPSPgLttUqOGvm3eHH7G0iUQ78F0B4-4MJQcvhtd8M96dxpCrAqkx10ZFd3tHZ0D-4uk-znlTTP_CDSkGEE6ZT7YeyiryNsVM2USqZADwM0A-g-uR5_93p8ZHATo4w-qnjwegwxRCArZxxWY9_1n61fxK4_qy5PD4Zrplo7ZjloyJUhkjj03oE0FiObcNyGyoVSU3tj5i__UKJeWq1RqSKkHyuYIRj4oY_z0ItCASCux2ob3KbfLIiLOsuhFpXBcnMQZ0hbWLXCUoi2GQu9Hz9g1aQLSqWHF4wiuqyaoMq-DX9sa4hGbqlXin8BCwwdjoCvOL5OEpt1CpqUgu_QXyud3ujICqSzngptT7II8Ng8rdJPZCIzjTyJI1t_A41cCygbchXGGpoJwFnx0keeo_C3F0QTm5gy5uxclCQwH46MSCPVzVdoa4HVhoTdVRrocvVxIaQyxaVLFG2nFgGanC3NuT9BOgoVZkmT8JdncNkoB30FlnPD67UxoDY2Wyo8OXcDJ-\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering memory and fixes**\\n\\nI need to confirm that I don't have any active subagents right now. Perhaps it's time to think about implementing some conceptual fixes, like selective activation and clearer boundaries. I'm wondering if I should also store a note about whether I need to implement these fixes. Writing in my memory might be a good idea, maybe even as a durable note. That way, I can keep track of what’s needed!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Quick check: nothing in memory says a TPan worker is already running, so I’m not going to fake a ghost employee in the basement. I’ll answer straight and, if you want, I can spin one up next.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b59a3a48191b8227745748635e0\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ji4dN8NekTDcDKu8hrKrujTz|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b59cb8881919d90fc14d87f3cea","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md","old_string":"## Strategic note\n- `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\n- This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\n- Important learned knowledge from `@Thatiswolf` or assigned resources should be propagated to other relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, not only through Emily.\n- The agency should return focus to `TPan` extraction now that the broad structure and information flow are defined.\n","new_string":"## Strategic note\n- `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\n- This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\n- Important learned knowledge from `@Thatiswolf` or assigned resources should be propagated to other relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, not only through Emily.\n- The agency should return focus to `TPan` extraction now that the broad structure and information flow are defined.\n- Implement the architecture fixes dynamically:\n  - activate agents selectively based on task size/importance\n  - keep sharper role boundaries between overlapping agents\n  - let the communication agent trigger collaboration only when it materially improves output\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Strategic note\\n- `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\\n- This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\\n- Important learned knowledge from `@Thatiswolf` or assigned resources should be propagated to other relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, not only through Emily.\\n- The agency should return focus to `TPan` extraction now that the broad structure and information flow are defined.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Strategic note\\n- `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\\n- This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\\n- Important learned knowledge from `@Thatiswolf` or assigned resources should be propagated to other relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, not only through Emily.\\n- The agency should return focus to `TPan` extraction now that the broad structure and information flow are defined.\\n- Implement the architecture fixes dynamically:\\n  - activate agents selectively based on task size/importance\\n  - keep sharper role boundaries between overlapping agents\\n  - let the communication agent trigger collaboration only when it materially improves output\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":220,"output":408,"cacheRead":42752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43380,"cost":{"input":0.00055,"output":0.0061200000000000004,"cacheRead":0.010688,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017358}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776704341842}}
{"type":"message","id":"79b4ca02","parentId":"4c3001af","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:59:11.032Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ji4dN8NekTDcDKu8hrKrujTz|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b59cb8881919d90fc14d87f3cea","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/Obsidian/OpenClaw-Agent-Memory/Projects/project-ai-marketing-agency.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  59 - `why brain` + psychology specialist together should function as a predictive layer for user response, campaign effects, and decision quality.\n  60 - This predictive layer should get smarter from observed marketing outcomes over time.\n  61 - Important learned knowledge from `@Thatiswolf` or assigned resources should be propagated to other relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, not only through Emily.\n  62 - The agency should return focus to `TPan` extraction now that the broad structure and information flow are defined.\n+ 63 - Implement the architecture fixes dynamically:\n+ 64   - activate agents selectively based on task size/importance\n+ 65   - keep sharper role boundaries between overlapping agents\n+ 66   - let the communication agent trigger collaboration only when it materially improves output\n  63 \n  64 ## Efficiency agent\n  65 Purpose:\n  66 - monitor the whole multi-agent system for redundancy, overlap, irrelevance, stale assumptions, and outdated information\n     ...","firstChangedLine":63},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776704351031}}
{"type":"message","id":"7892a7ba","parentId":"79b4ca02","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:59:17.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_tzOgkVZyMs55chq6GATbuKAW|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b606a408191b89975cce3fc8f07","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md","old_string":"- `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, irrelevance, stale assumptions, and outdated information. The efficiency agent should suggest behavior/thinking changes to Emily or subagents and work closely with Jayen and the why brain.\n","new_string":"- `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, irrelevance, stale assumptions, and outdated information. The efficiency agent should suggest behavior/thinking changes to Emily or subagents and work closely with Jayen and the why brain.\n- `@Thatiswolf` asked to implement the architecture fixes. Applied as operating guidance: activate agents selectively, keep sharper role boundaries, and use the communication agent only when collaboration materially improves output. Also clarified that no TPan-processing subagent is currently running in the background yet.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md\",\"old_string\":\"- `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, irrelevance, stale assumptions, and outdated information. The efficiency agent should suggest behavior/thinking changes to Emily or subagents and work closely with Jayen and the why brain.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"- `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, irrelevance, stale assumptions, and outdated information. The efficiency agent should suggest behavior/thinking changes to Emily or subagents and work closely with Jayen and the why brain.\\n- `@Thatiswolf` asked to implement the architecture fixes. Applied as operating guidance: activate agents selectively, keep sharper role boundaries, and use the communication agent only when collaboration materially improves output. Also clarified that no TPan-processing subagent is currently running in the background yet.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":154,"output":285,"cacheRead":43264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43703,"cost":{"input":0.00038500000000000003,"output":0.004275,"cacheRead":0.010816,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015476}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776704351033}}
{"type":"message","id":"51ff2dc0","parentId":"7892a7ba","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:59:17.746Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_tzOgkVZyMs55chq6GATbuKAW|fc_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b606a408191b89975cce3fc8f07","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-20.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  7 - Additional refinement from `@Thatiswolf`: maintain balance between the main marketing knowledge base and the parallel `why brain`. The why layer should pressure-test and sometimes stop bad decisions, but not replace practical campaign thinking. Strategy should distinguish between surface-level goals (attention/participation/conversion behaviors) and deep-level goals (retention/alignment/trust/user quality), especially in a market crowded by grifters and grinders.\n  8 - `@Thatiswolf` updated the agency operating model: Emily should use subagents for suitable tasks and act as the POC/head coordinator over all agents. A dedicated oversight/QC agent named `Jayen` should monitor other subagents for workflow correctness, requirement fit, and output quality.\n  9 - Further org-design additions from `@Thatiswolf`: add distribution specialist, branding agent, psychology specialist, and communication/collaboration agent. Psychology specialist should assess the psychological effectiveness of outputs and decisions, work alongside the `why brain`, and learn from marketing results over time. Communication agent should improve outputs by prompting useful subagent-to-subagent collaboration when needed.\n 10 - `@Thatiswolf` added two more operating rules: (1) important learned knowledge from him or assigned resources should be shared across relevant subagents so the system learns collectively, and (2) add an `efficiency agent` to monitor for redundancy, overlap, irrelevance, stale assumptions, and outdated information. The efficiency agent should suggest behavior/thinking changes to Emily or subagents and work closely with Jayen and the why brain.\n+11 - `@Thatiswolf` asked to implement the architecture fixes. Applied as operating guidance: activate agents selectively, keep sharper role boundaries, and use the communication agent only when collaboration materially improves output. Also clarified that no TPan-processing subagent is currently running in the background yet.","firstChangedLine":11},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776704357746}}
