{"type":"message","id":"d9ec446a","parentId":"304844f5","timestamp":"2026-04-20T16:59:29.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] yes — I’ve implemented the fixes as operating rules:\n\n- **selective activation** instead of waking the whole zoo for every small task\n- **sharper role boundaries** between overlapping agents\n- **communication agent only when useful**, not as mandatory ceremony\n\n### TPan status right now\nhonest answer: **I have not yet gone through all the articles**.\n\nCurrent status is:\n- I identified TPan as the assigned training source\n- I checked the homepage / feed level to understand the source type\n- I designed the extraction framework and full multi-agent processing architecture\n- I stored the agency rules, knowledge flow, and subagent structure\n\nBut:\n- **full archive processing is not running yet**\n- **no subagent is actively processing TPan in the background right now**\n\n### Which subagent is doing it actively right now?\n**none at the moment.**\n\nI hadn’t spawned one yet because until now we were still defining:\n- the architecture\n- the learning standard\n- the why-brain logic\n- the subagent org structure\n- QA / efficiency / communication roles\n\nSo the system design was being built first before execution.\n\n### What should do TPan work once active?\nBest active setup would be:\n\n- **Research agent** → read/archive/extract article facts\n- **Why brain** → causal layer\n- **Psychology specialist** → user-response layer\n- **Efficiency agent** → dedupe/compress/clean\n- **Jayen** → QA check\n- **Emily** → final synthesis + memory propagation\n\nThat is the lean version.\n\nIf you want, I can **start the background TPan pipeline now** by spinning up:\n1. a **TPan research subagent**\n2. a **Jayen reviewer**\n3. optionally an **efficiency pass**\n\nThen I can report progress as it learns through the archive.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0956d56a4dd30d7c0169e65b69fa9481919c420b5e12d366a5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":322,"output":390,"cacheRead":43648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44360,"cost":{"input":0.000805,"output":0.00585,"cacheRead":0.010912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017567}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776704360699}}
