aw/workspace. Goal: begin processing TPan's Substack (https://tpan.substack.com/) as a crypto/web3 marketing knowledge source. Use available web tools to inspect the feed/archive and start extracting insights from the earliest accessible articles first if possible, otherwise proceed with accessible articles in a consistent order. For each article you process, produce a compact structured result with: title, url, date if available, core topic, surface insight, why, market context, user behavior pattern, GTM implication, product implication if any, prediction value, durability (timely/cyclical/evergreen), and confidence. Keep outputs concise but useful. Do not pretend to have processed articles you could not access. Save interim findings to a workspace file at tpan/intake-batch-01.md, appending as you go. Also include a short progress header at the top with number of articles processed and blockers. Commit workspace changes when you make meaningful progress. Return a concise progress summary when done or when you hit a natural checkpoint.","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace","mode":"session","thread":false,"streamTo":"parent","timeoutSeconds":600,"cleanup":"keep","sandbox":"inherit"},"partialJson":"{\"label\":\"tpan-research\",\"runtime\":\"subagent\",\"task\":\"You are the TPan research subagent for an AI marketing agency. Work inside /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace. Goal: begin processing TPan's Substack (https://tpan.substack.com/) as a crypto/web3 marketing knowledge source. Use available web tools to inspect the feed/archive and start extracting insights from the earliest accessible articles first if possible, otherwise proceed with accessible articles in a consistent order. For each article you process, produce a compact structured result with: title, url, date if available, core topic, surface insight, why, market context, user behavior pattern, GTM implication, product implication if any, prediction value, durability (timely/cyclical/evergreen), and conf